Full Title: Applied Linguistics & Language Teaching 
Short Title: ALLT 

Date: 16-Apr-2009 - 18-Apr-2009
Location: Taipei, Taiwan 
Contact Person: Claire Ho
Meeting Email: allt@mail.ntust.edu.tw
Web Site: http://www.afl.ntust.edu.tw/p0.htm 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Language Acquisition; Translation 

Call Deadline: 20-Dec-2008 

Meeting Description:

2009 International Conference on Applied Linguistics & Language Teaching (ALLT)
held by Department of Applied Foreign Languages, National Taiwan University of
Science & Technology (NTUST), Taipei, Taiwan

Time: April 16-18, 2009
Site: National Taiwan University of Science & Technology (NTUST), Taipei, Taiwan 

Call for Papers

Conference Themes:TESL, TCSL, Interpretation & Translation
Second language acquisition (SLA): Theory and application
Corpus/Corpora in Language Application & Teaching  
CALL and Web in Applied Linguistics and Language Teaching 
Cross Culture and Literature in Language Teaching 
Language testing & assessment 
Language for Specific Purposes (LSP) in Application & Teaching 
Teaching Chinese as a Second Language (TCSL): Trends and Challenges 
Educational objectives of applied English / foreign language programs 
Translator and interpreter training theories and practices. 
Other relevant topics are also welcome. 

Plenary, Featured and/or Keynote Speakers
1. Professor William Wang (Chinese University of Hong Kong, fellow, Academia Sinica)
2. Professor Chin-Chuan Cheng (University of Illinois, fellow, Academia Sinica) 
3. Professor Amy Tsui (Pro-Vice Chancellor, Hong Kong University)
4. Professor Burnard Lou (Oxford University Press, UK)
5. Professor Mike Scott (School of English, University of Liverpool, UK)
6. Professor Ik-Sang Eom (Dean, School of Foreign Languages, Hanyang University,
Korea)
7. Professor Xin-Chang Yang (Dean, School of Foreign Languages, Xiamen University)
8. Professor Ping Chen (School of Languages, University of Queensland, Australia)
9. Professor Martin Bygate (Department of Linguistics, University of Lancaster)
(to be confirmed)
10. Prof. Mariachiara Russo (President of Degree Course of Interpreting,
University of Bologna, Italy)
11. Professor Tzeng, Ovid (Fellow, Academia Sinica)

Featured Colloquiums, Workshops and Activities
1. Papers, workshops, and colloquiums (3-4 persons as a team preferred): Eunice
Shih, Wuchang Chang, Chioulan Chen, Shuogui Joe, Hsinan Yeh, Yuling You; Yea-fen
Chen, etc.
2. Methodology: qualitative vs. quantitative
3. Seminar for journal papers: writing and submission
4. Speech Contest

Conference Proceedings to be published by Crane Publishing Co., Taiwan; selected
papers will be considered for the Journal
Conference Organization: Department of Applied Foreign Languages, NTUST
Conference Venue: National Taiwan University of Science & Technology, Taiwan, R.O.C.
Banquet: Howard International House, Taipei
(http://intl-house.howard-hotels.com.tw/), April 18, 2009

